##Components Used

1)BC547 Transistor
2)IR Receiver LED + IR Emitter LED (IR Module)
3)10KΩ Resistor
4)1KΩ Resistor
5)220Ω Resistor
6)Red LED
7)3V Water Pump with Pipe + Plastic Container
8)Switch
9)3.7V Li-ion Battery
10)TP4056 Charging Module
11)Jumper Wires

##Working Principle

1)The IR flame sensor detects fire (flame changes IR light intensity).
2)The sensor output goes through resistor biasing into a BC547 transistor.
3)The transistor acts as a switch:

 i)Turns ON Red LED (fire alert)
 ii)Activates Water Pump to spray water

4)Once the flame is gone, the sensor output returns to normal, and the pump stops.


